               <property name="text">
                <string>Chemistry simplifier converts a series of compositional/microanalytical maps (SEM-EDX, XFM) into dimensionally reduced representation images (RGB). For convenience, the user cannot input less than 3 images. Previously calculated models can be loaded and reused for scalability (accross thin sections). The interface functionality conceptualised by  Acevedo Zamora et al. (2024) (https://github.com/marcoaaz/AcevedoEtAl._2024b_autoencoder) was updated for parallel processing. Image alignment requires a control point CSV file similar to ImageJ BigWarp plugin.</string>
